- Normalized citation markers from `^n^` to Markdown footnotes (`[^n]`) throughout the body.
- Converted the `# References` section into proper footnote definitions (`[^n]: ...`) so citations render cleanly in Markdown/Hugo.
- Fixed one malformed numbered subsection under `**Remarks:**` into proper Markdown list formatting (`1.`, `2.`, `3.`).
- Minor spacing cleanup around inline footnote mentions (e.g., `reference [^5]`).

No abstract duplication was found in the body, and no LaTeX/KaTeX/math content was modified.
